<h3 id="wyn_email_publish">wyn_email_publish</h3>

<p><strong>Description</strong></p>

<p>When you publish a new post, this plugin will mail it to everywhere (email address of course :D) you want.</p>

<p>That means, you can publish the post onto other BSPs, which support email publish feature (like live space, or blogger), just as the same time you publish on textpattern.</p>

<p><strong>History</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>0.2: Add admin config panel, you can not only set the email addresses here, but also customize the content of mail</li>
  <li>0.1: Initialize Release, just has basal function, a little troublesome to use</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Usage</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>Install and active it, and of course, set up your email publish function of your BSPs</li>
  <li>Go to extenstion -&gt; Email Publish</li>
  <li>Now you can set the mail address, use â€˜;â€™ to separator if you have more than one address</li>
  <li>Set the title and body of mail, you can use the tag <em>title</em>, <em>body</em>, <em>author</em> and <em>link</em> to replace the title, the content, the author name and the link of the article. 
(<strong>NOTICE</strong>: <em>link</em> and <em>body</em> are <strong>NOT</strong> allowed in mail title)</li>
  <li>Go to write a new post to introduce this little thing :D</li>
</ul>

<p>Download <a href="http://code.google.com/p/wyn-txp-plugins/downloads/list">here</a></p>

